OL,3,CBid to decriminalise cannabis in
OL,4,CJersey defeated by single vote
OL,6,F22 politicians voted in favour of the
OL,7,Fmove while 23 voted against and one
OL,8,FStates Member abstained.
OL,10,FFormer Health Minister, Deputy Karen
OL,11,FWilson, argued that agreeing to the
OL,12,Fidea would have meant "unleashing a
OL,13,Fharmful experiment on the mental and
OL,14,Fphysical health of the people of
OL,15,FJersey".
